Installation:

ESTER is available under the GPL Version 3 license. It is hosted either on
google code site (https://code.google.com/p/ester-project) or on github
(https://github.com/ester-project/ester).

To use the last version of the code, you can directly clone the last
development version form Git:

shell$ git clone https://github.com/ester-project/ester.git
shell$ cd ester
./bootstrap

Installation of the ESTER binaries and library use the common GNU-based
process:
shell$ ./configure --prefix=...
shell$ make
shell$ make install

In order to use the ester library and binaries, do not forget add the
installation directories to your PATH, LD_LIBRARY_PATH and CPATH environement
variables.
For instance, if you used $HOME/local as the install prefix (during the
configure process), you should add $HOME/local/lib to your LD_LIBRARY_PATH,
$HOME/local/include to your CPATH and $HOME/local/bin to you PATH.

